The moron that shoots his gun in the air on Independence Day wasn't trying to kill 6,000 people was he?  The terrorists were.  An accident made out of idiocy and an act of unprovoked war are two totally different issues.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Why not drop a billion dollars worth of food instead of a billion dollars of bombs? Why not use our vast military might to quarantine the country and slowly squeeze it tighter and tighter until the only thing left in our hands are those responsible for this atrocity? Why not arm the Northern Alliance to its teeth, and then support them to oust the Taliban and arrest Bin Laden? Why not use our supposedly overwhelming military and technological superiority to find these folks, cave by cave, and hunt them down with Black Ops? Etc., etc. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
